\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.1}{\ignorespaces Three-layer system architecture. Sensor data flows through the LSTM deep ensemble (Layer~1), which produces both a mean RUL prediction and an uncertainty signal. Both are observed by the DQN agent (Layer~2), whose proposed action is subject to the safety supervisor's (Layer~3) two-tier override logic before execution. The dashed line indicates the uncertainty signal also feeding into the supervisor's confidence check.}}{15}{figure.3.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:arch}{{3.1}{15}{Three-layer system architecture. Sensor data flows through the LSTM deep ensemble (Layer~1), which produces both a mean RUL prediction and an uncertainty signal. Both are observed by the DQN agent (Layer~2), whose proposed action is subject to the safety supervisor's (Layer~3) two-tier override logic before execution. The dashed line indicates the uncertainty signal also feeding into the supervisor's confidence check}{figure.3.1}{}}
